# Real Interview Answer

**Interviewer:** Explain your deployment pipeline.

**Answer:**

> "After developers pushed code to GitHub, our GitHub Actions workflow executed on a self-hosted runner. The CI pipeline built the frontend and backend Docker images, verified them, and scanned them using Trivy. Once the pipeline succeeded, GitHub Actions deployed the application to our Kubernetes cluster using `kubectl apply`. Kubernetes compared the desired state in the YAML file with the running cluster, created new ReplicaSets if needed, and performed rolling updates. We configured liveness and readiness probes to ensure only healthy Pods received traffic, and Kubernetes supported rollback in case a deployment failed."

